{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"","text":"<p>Welcome to T1nk3r, your ultimate guide to navigating the realms of DevOps, SRE, and creating efficient homelabs. Whether you're a seasoned professional looking to refine your skills or a curious enthusiast starting your journey, you've landed in the right place. Here, I curate practical insights, tutorials, and resources to empower you in mastering the art of infrastructure automation, reliable software deployment, and optimizing your home setup. Let's embark together on this transformative journey into the world of modern IT practices and home technology integration.</p> <p>Just so you know</p> <p>This documentation is a curation of all that i've learned over the years of tinkering and resolving infrastructure issues. Enjoy  </p>"},{"location":"sections/devops/argocd/","title":"ArgoCD","text":""},{"location":"sections/devops/argocd/#retrieve-argo-cd-admin-password","title":"Retrieve Argo CD admin Password","text":"<pre><code>kubectl -n {namespace} get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" | base64 -d\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/","title":"Docker","text":""},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#build-docker-image","title":"Build Docker Image","text":"<pre><code>docker build -t &lt;app&gt; .\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#view-all-docker-images","title":"View all docker images","text":"<p><pre><code>docker images\n</code></pre> <pre><code>docker image ls\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#run-docker-image","title":"Run Docker Image","text":"<pre><code>docker run &lt;image name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#run-in-detached-state","title":"Run in detached state","text":"<pre><code>docker run -d &lt;image name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#run-with-your-specified-name","title":"Run with your specified name","text":"<pre><code>docker run -d --name &lt;unique name&gt; &lt;image name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#view-all-docker-containers","title":"View all docker containers","text":"<pre><code>docker ps -a\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#view-all-running-docker-containers","title":"View all running docker containers","text":"<pre><code>docker ps\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#remove-single-image","title":"Remove single image","text":"<pre><code>docker image remove &lt;image-name&gt;:&lt;tag&gt;\ndocker image rm &lt;image-name&gt;\ndocker image rm &lt;id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#force-remove-running-container","title":"Force remove running container","text":"<pre><code>docker rm -f &lt;container-id&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#tag-an-image","title":"Tag an Image","text":"<pre><code>docker image tag &lt;image-name&gt;:&lt;tag&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#specific-guides","title":"Specific Guides","text":"<p>Cleaning up Images &amp; Containers</p> <p>Pushing image to dockerhub</p> <ol> <li>Get acess token from dockerhub website </li> <li>Authenticate using  <pre><code>docker login -u NAME\n</code></pre></li> <li>Enter Token </li> <li>Tag the docker image to prepare for push     <pre><code>docker image tag &lt;image-name&gt; &lt;dockerhub-username&gt;/&lt;image-name&gt;:&lt;tag&gt;\n</code></pre></li> <li>Push image using  <pre><code>docker image push &lt;dockerhub-username&gt;/&lt;image-name&gt;:&lt;tag&gt;\n</code></pre></li> </ol> <p>Docker Volumes</p> <p>Run docker with volume attached</p> <p>Ensure $user has elevated privildeges to open folder</p> <pre><code>docker run -d -p &lt;host-port&gt;:&lt;container-port&gt; -v path-data:/path/data &lt;image-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#clean-dangling-images","title":"Clean dangling images","text":"<pre><code>docker image prune\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#clean-stopped-containers","title":"Clean stopped containers","text":"<pre><code>docker container prune\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#create-docker-volume","title":"Create docker volume","text":"<pre><code>docker volume create &lt;volume-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/docker/#inspect-docker-volume","title":"Inspect docker volume","text":"<pre><code>docker volume inspect &lt;volume-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/iam-policies/iam-policies/","title":"Cloudfront Access Policy","text":"<pre><code>{\n    \"Version\": \"2008-10-17\",\n    \"Id\": \"PolicyForCloudFrontPrivateContent\",\n    \"Statement\": [\n        {\n            \"Sid\": \"AllowCloudFrontServicePrincipal\",\n            \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n            \"Principal\": {\n                \"Service\": \"cloudfront.amazonaws.com\"\n            },\n            \"Action\": \"s3:GetObject\",\n            \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:s3:::{bucket-name}/*\",\n            \"Condition\": {\n                \"StringEquals\": {\n                    \"AWS:SourceArn\": \"arn:aws:cloudfront::{account-id}:distribution/{distribution-id}\"\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    ]\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/devops/iam-policies/iam-policies/#single-user-s3-access-policy","title":"Single User S3 Access Policy","text":"<pre><code>{\n    \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",\n    \"Statement\": [\n        {\n            \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n            \"Principal\": {\n                \"AWS\": \"arn:aws:iam::{account-id}:user/{user}\"\n            },\n            \"Action\": \"s3:*\",\n            \"Resource\": [\n                \"arn:aws:s3:::{bucket-name}\",\n                \"arn:aws:s3:::{bucket-name}/*\"\n            ]\n        }\n    ]\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/cmd-prompt/","title":"Command Prompt","text":""},{"location":"sections/scripting/cmd-prompt/#install-a-windows-service","title":"Install a windows service","text":"<pre><code>sc create name_of_the_service binPath=\"path\\to\\theexecutable.exe\" DisplayName=\"name_of_the_service\"\n</code></pre> <p>Tip</p> <p>Since this is an admin features, make sure to run this in an elevated window.  You can also create multiple services at once using a <code>.cmd</code> file and runing it once</p>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/cmd-prompt/#install-an-nservice-bus-service-in-windows","title":"Install an NService Bus service in windows","text":"<pre><code>\"path\\to\\ServiceBusHost.exe\" /install /serviceName:name_of_the_service /displayName:\"name_of_the_service\"\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/powershell/","title":"Powershell","text":""},{"location":"sections/scripting/powershell/#get-list-of-all-installed-windows-server-optional-features","title":"Get list of all installed windows server optional features","text":"<pre><code>Get-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online | where {$_.state -eq \"Enabled\"} | ft -Property featurename\n</code></pre> <p>Tip</p> <p>Since these are admin features, make sure to run this in an elevated window.  You can also output to a file by pipeing result using below command <pre><code>| Out-File -FilePath \"path\\tofile.txt\"\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/powershell/#how-to-kill-a-process","title":"How to kill a process","text":"<pre><code>taskkill /f /pid &lt;pid&gt;\n</code></pre> <p>Tip</p> <p>Make sure to find the pid using Task Manager and replace <code>&lt;pid&gt;</code> with the unique value. </p>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/powershell/#set-time-and-date-to-specific-time-zone","title":"Set time and date to specific time zone","text":"<pre><code>Set-TimeZone -Name \"Central Standard Time\"\n</code></pre> <p>Tip</p> <p>This is an admin feature, run in elevated window.  Use <code>Get-TimeZone</code> to know which one you are currently set to. Use <code>Get-TimeZone -ListAvailable</code> to get all possible time zones you can apply. </p>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/powershell/#unzip-multiple-files-into-a-single-location","title":"Unzip multiple files into a single location","text":""},{"location":"sections/scripting/powershell/#set-a-single-service-account-to-multiple-windows-services","title":"Set a single service account to multiple windows services","text":""},{"location":"sections/scripting/python/","title":"Python","text":""},{"location":"sections/scripting/python/#setting-up-a-virtual-environment","title":"Setting up a virtual environment","text":"<p>Note</p> <p>Ensure you have python installed for this to work.  Download Python here </p>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/python/#windows","title":"Windows","text":"<pre><code>```\nmkdir &lt;yourdir&gt;\ncd &lt;yourdir&gt;\npy -3 -m venv env\nenv\\scripts\\activate\n```\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/python/#mac-linux","title":"Mac / Linux","text":"<pre><code>```\nmkdir &lt;yourdir&gt;\ncd &lt;yourdir&gt;\npython3 -m venv venv\nsource venv/bin/activate\n```\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/python/#generate-requirements-files","title":"Generate requirements files","text":"<pre><code>pip3 freeze &gt; requirements.txt\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/scripting/python/#fix-pip-env-error","title":"Fix pip env error","text":"<pre><code>python -m pip install --upgrade pip\npython -m pip install --upgrade --force-reinstall pip\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/aws-cli/","title":"aws-cli","text":""},{"location":"sections/utilities/aws-cli/#connect-to-eks-cluster","title":"Connect to eks cluster","text":"<pre><code>aws eks update-kubeconfig --region &lt;region-code&gt; --name &lt;my-cluster&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/eksctl/","title":"eksctl","text":"<p>Info</p> <p>This is not a subsititute for eksctl core documentation.  EKS CTL documentation</p>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/eksctl/#create-cluster-from-manifest-file","title":"Create Cluster from manifest file","text":"<pre><code>eksctl create cluster -f &lt;filename.yaml&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/eksctl/#delete-cluster-from-manifest-file","title":"Delete Cluster from manifest file","text":"<pre><code>eksctl delete cluster -f &lt;filename.yaml&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/eksctl/#scale-up-a-cluster-nodes-directly-from-cli","title":"Scale up a cluster nodes directly from CLI","text":"<pre><code>eksctl scale nodegroup --cluster [Cluster Name]--name [Nodegroup name] --nodes 2 --nodes-max 2 --nodes-min 1 \n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/eksctl/#see-all-node-groups","title":"See all Node Groups","text":"<pre><code>eksctl get nodegroups --cluster &lt;cluster-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/eksctl/#delete-node-groups","title":"Delete Node groups","text":"<pre><code>eksctl delete nodegroup --cluster &lt;cluster-name&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/git/","title":"git","text":""},{"location":"sections/utilities/git/#delete-all-local-branches-except-mainmaster","title":"Delete all local branches except main/master","text":"<pre><code>git branch | grep -v \"main\" | xargs git branch -D\n</code></pre> <p>Tip</p> <p>Replace main with branch of your choice</p>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/gpg/","title":"gpg","text":""},{"location":"sections/utilities/gpg/#import-keys","title":"Import Keys","text":"<pre><code>gpg --import &lt;file&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/gpg/#encrypt-file","title":"Encrypt File","text":"<pre><code>gpg -e &lt;file&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/gpg/#decrypt-file-to-a-specific-output-name","title":"Decrypt file to a specific output name","text":"<pre><code>gpg --output &lt;outfile&gt; -d &lt;encrypted file&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/kubectl/","title":"kubectl","text":""},{"location":"sections/utilities/kubectl/#change-name-of-cluster-context","title":"Change name of cluster context","text":"<pre><code>kubectl config rename-context old-name new-name\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"sections/utilities/kubectl/#get-cluster-contexts","title":"Get cluster contexts","text":"<pre><code>kubectl config get-contexts \n</code></pre>"}]}